---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cheshire House Prices by Area and Property Type | movetocheshire.uk"
  description="Cheshire averages £314,000 (ONS, 2025). Prices by unitary authority, town, ward, and property type - detached, semi-detached, terraced, flat - from ONS, Rightmove, and council data."
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(webPageSchema)} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(breadcrumbSchema)} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  </Fragment>

  <!-- Breadcrumb -->
  <div class="section-pad" style="padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 0;">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; color: #999999;">
        <a href="/" style="color: #999999; text-decoration: none;">Home</a>
        <span style="margin: 0 8px;">/</span>
        <span style="color: #1C1C1E;">House Prices</span>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section-pad" style="padding-top: 40px;">
    <div class="section-inner" style="max-width: 720px;">
      <span class="section-label">Property Data</span>
      <h1 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(28px, 4.5vw, 44px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.15; margin: 0 0 20px 0; letter-spacing: -0.02em;">
        Cheshire House Prices by Area and Property Type
      </h1>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 24px 0;">
        Cheshire averages £314,000 across all property types (PlumPlot/ONS, 2025), 8% above the UK national average of £290,000. Prices range from £115,000 in Ellesmere Port to £1,163,360 for a detached home in Alderley Edge. Data by unitary authority, town, ward, and property type from ONS, Rightmove, and council sources.
      </p>
      <span style="display: inline-block; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: #3D5A3E; background-color: rgba(61, 90, 62, 0.08); padding: 6px 12px; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">Last updated: February 2026</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stat Bar -->
  <section class="section-pad" style="padding-top: 0;">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 20px;">
        {stats.map((stat) => (
          <div style="background-color: #FFFFFF; border: 1px solid #E5E0D8; padding: 28px 24px;">
            <p class="data-tile-value" style="margin: 0 0 8px 0;">{stat.value}</p>
            <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 4px 0;">{stat.label}</p>
            <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: #999999; margin: 0;">{stat.source}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick Answer -->
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="section-inner" style="max-width: 720px;">
      <span class="section-label">The short answer</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 24px 0;">How much does a house cost in Cheshire?</h2>
      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px;">
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0;">Cheshire averages £314,000 across all property types (PlumPlot/ONS, 2025), with a median of £255,000. Cheshire East averages £306,000 (ONS, Dec 2025), up 5.7% year-on-year. Cheshire West and Chester averages £266,000, up 2.8%. Warrington averages £252,000, up 6.0%.</p>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0;">Cheshire has 34% detached housing stock versus 22% nationally (Census 2021), which pulls the county average above the UK figure of £290,000. A detached home in Cheshire East averages £496,000. A terraced home in Cheshire West averages £207,000. A flat in Halton averages £103,000.</p>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0;">Cheshire prices range from £115,000 in Ellesmere Port Westminster ward to £1,163,360 for a detached home in Alderley Edge (Rightmove/CW&C Council, 2023-2026). That £1,048,360 spread within a single county explains why the headline average misleads without area and property type context.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Unitary Authority Comparison -->
  <section class="section-pad" style="background-color: #FFFFFF; border-top: 1px solid #E5E0D8; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8;">
    <div class="section-inner" style="max-width: 900px;">
      <span class="section-label">By authority</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">What are house prices in each Cheshire authority area?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 28px 0;">Cheshire splits into four unitary authorities with distinct price profiles. Cheshire East commands the highest average at £306,000 (ONS, Dec 2025). Halton at £189,000 is the most affordable, 35% below the county average.</p>
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px;">
        {authorities.map((auth) => (
          <div style="border-left: 3px solid #3D5A3E; background-color: #F9F7F4; padding: 24px;">
            <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 4px 0;">{auth.name}</p>
            <p style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 28px; font-weight: 700; color: #3D5A3E; margin: 0 0 2px 0;">{auth.price}</p>
            <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #C4933F; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">{auth.growth} YoY</p>
            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 8px;">
              <div><p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: #999999; margin: 0;">Detached</p><p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0;">{auth.detached}</p></div>
              <div><p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: #999999; margin: 0;">Semi</p><p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0;">{auth.semi}</p></div>
              <div><p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: #999999; margin: 0;">Terraced</p><p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0;">{auth.terraced}</p></div>
              <div><p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: #999999; margin: 0;">Flat</p><p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0;">{auth.flat}</p></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: #999999; margin: 16px 0 0 0;">Source: ONS UK House Price Index, December 2025. Year-on-year growth compares Dec 2025 to Dec 2024.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Golden Triangle -->
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="section-inner" style="max-width: 900px;">
      <span class="section-label">Premium towns</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">What do houses cost in the Golden Triangle?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 28px 0;">The Golden Triangle - Alderley Edge, Wilmslow, and Knutsford - commands the highest prices in the North West. Alderley Edge detached homes average £1,163,360, 135% above the Cheshire East detached average of £496,000 (Rightmove, 12 months to Feb 2026).</p>
      <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
        <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; min-width: 600px;">
          <thead>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid #3D5A3E;">
              {['Town', 'Average', 'Detached', 'Semi', 'Terraced', 'Flat'].map((col) => (
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: #1C1C1E;">{col}</th>
              ))}
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {goldenTriangle.map((town, i) => (
              <tr style={`background-color: ${i % 2 === 0 ? '#FFFFFF' : '#F9F7F4'}; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8;`}>
                <td style="padding: 14px 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: #1C1C1E;">{town.name}</td>
                <td style="padding: 14px 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; color: #3D5A3E;">{town.avg}</td>
                <td style="padding: 14px 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: #444444;">{town.detached}</td>
                <td style="padding: 14px 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: #444444;">{town.semi}</td>
                <td style="padding: 14px 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: #444444;">{town.terraced}</td>
                <td style="padding: 14px 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: #444444;">{town.flat}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: #999999; margin: 12px 0 0 0;">Source: Rightmove, 12 months to early 2026. Poynton verified via data.md. "-" indicates insufficient transaction data for that property type.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Property Type Breakdown -->
  <section class="section-pad" style="background-color: #FFFFFF; border-top: 1px solid #E5E0D8; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8;">
    <div class="section-inner" style="max-width: 900px;">
      <span class="section-label">By property type</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">How much does each property type cost in Cheshire?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 28px 0;">Cheshire detached homes average £496,000 county-wide (ONS, Dec 2025). Flats average £170,000, a £326,000 difference that reflects the county's high proportion of detached stock at 34% versus 22% nationally (Census 2021).</p>
      <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
        <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; min-width: 550px;">
          <thead>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid #3D5A3E;">
              {['Area', 'Detached', 'Semi-detached', 'Terraced', 'Flat'].map((col) => (
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: #1C1C1E;">{col}</th>
              ))}
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {[...propertyTypes, ...selectedWardTypes].map((row, i) => (
              <tr style={`background-color: ${i % 2 === 0 ? '#FFFFFF' : '#F9F7F4'}; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8; ${i === 4 ? 'border-bottom: 2px solid #E5E0D8;' : ''}`}>
                <td style={`padding: 14px 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: ${i < 5 ? '600' : '500'}; color: #1C1C1E;`}>{row.area}</td>
                <td style="padding: 14px 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: #444444;">{row.detached}</td>
                <td style="padding: 14px 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: #444444;">{row.semi}</td>
                <td style="padding: 14px 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: #444444;">{row.terraced}</td>
                <td style="padding: 14px 12px; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: #444444;">{row.flat}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: #999999; margin: 12px 0 0 0;">Source: ONS UK HPI Dec 2025 (authority rows). Rightmove 12 months to Feb 2026 (town rows). CW&C Council 2023 (Frodsham, Helsby, Northwich). "-" = insufficient data.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Cheshire West Ward Prices -->
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="section-inner" style="max-width: 900px;">
      <span class="section-label">Ward-level data</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">What are house prices in each Cheshire West ward?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 28px 0;">Cheshire West and Chester ward-level prices range from £115,000 in Ellesmere Port Westminster to £487,500 in Tattenhall (CW&C Council, 2023). Chester wards span from £172,000 in Blacon to £340,000 in Handbridge Park and Upton.</p>
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr)); gap: 8px;">
        {cheshireWestTowns.map((town) => (
          <div style={`padding: 16px; border-left: 3px solid ${town.level === 'premium' ? '#C4933F' : town.level === 'high' ? '#3D5A3E' : town.level === 'mid' ? '#6B8F71' : '#8BA38F'}; background-color: #F9F7F4;`}>
            <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 4px 0;">{town.name}</p>
            <p style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0;">{town.price}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: #999999; margin: 12px 0 0 0;">Source: Cheshire West and Chester Council ward-level median prices, 2023. Northwich overall average: £242,657 (Rightmove, Mar 2025). Gold = premium (£450k+), dark green = high (£300-449k), mid green = mid (£200-299k), light green = affordable (under £200k).</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Relocator Questions -->
  <section class="section-pad" style="background-color: #FFFFFF; border-top: 1px solid #E5E0D8; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8;">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-label">From the community</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">What do relocators from London and the South East ask about Cheshire prices?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 28px 0;">London averages £551,294 (ONS, Dec 2025). Cheshire averages £314,000. Relocators from southern England gain 45-60% more floor space per pound in Cheshire towns outside the Golden Triangle (Rightmove, 2025).</p>
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(320px, 1fr)); gap: 20px;">
        {[
          { initials: 'RB', name: 'R.B.', location: 'Moving from Surrey', question: "We have a budget of £550,000. In Surrey that buys a tired three-bed semi. What does the same money get in Cheshire?", answer: "In Knutsford (£606,876 average), £550,000 reaches a four-bedroom semi-detached or a modest detached on a quieter street. In Northwich (£242,657 average), £550,000 buys a new-build five-bedroom detached with garden and double garage. In Macclesfield or Chester Newton and Hoole, the same budget reaches a large detached four-bedroom. In Wilmslow (£489,105 average), £550,000 reaches a three-bedroom semi or a two-bedroom apartment in a premium location.", colour: '#3D5A3E' },
          { initials: 'MH', name: 'M.H.', location: 'Moving from North London', question: "Rightmove prices for Alderley Edge look comparable to Zone 4 London. Is there a price advantage anywhere in Cheshire?", answer: "Alderley Edge at £666,489 average is the exception. Detached homes there average £1,163,360 (Rightmove, Feb 2026), approaching outer London levels. Knutsford detached homes average £880,000 - 24% below Alderley Edge. Chester city wards average £205,000-£340,000 depending on neighbourhood. Northwich averages £242,657. A budget of £700,000 in Zone 4 London typically buys a semi-detached. In Knutsford the same budget reaches a four-bedroom detached with gardens.", colour: '#C4933F' },
        ].map((card) => (
          <div style={`background-color: #F9F7F4; border-left: 3px solid ${card.colour}; padding: 28px 24px;`}>
            <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 16px;">
              <div style={`width: 40px; height: 40px; border-radius: 50%; background-color: ${card.colour}; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; color: #FFFFFF; flex-shrink: 0;`}>{card.initials}</div>
              <div>
                <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0;">{card.name}</p>
                <span style={`font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; color: ${card.colour}; background-color: ${card.colour}15; padding: 2px 8px; letter-spacing: 0.02em;`}>{card.location}</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.65; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0; font-style: italic;">"{card.question}"</p>
            <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0;">{card.answer}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Accordion -->
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="section-inner" style="max-width: 800px;">
      <span class="section-label">Common questions</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">What do buyers ask about Cheshire house prices?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 28px 0;">Cheshire house price questions answered with ONS UK HPI (Dec 2025), Rightmove (Feb 2026), and CW&C Council ward data (2023).</p>
      <div style="border-top: 2px solid #3D5A3E;">
        {faqs.map((faq) => (
          <details style="border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8;">
            <summary style="padding: 20px 0; cursor: pointer; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.4; list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; gap: 16px;">
              {faq.q}
              <span style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 20px; color: #C4933F; flex-shrink: 0;">+</span>
            </summary>
            <div style="padding-bottom: 24px;">
              <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0;">{faq.a}</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Spoke Cards -->
  <section class="section-pad" style="background-color: #FFFFFF; border-top: 1px solid #E5E0D8; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8;">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-label">Detailed guides</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">Which Cheshire house price guides go deeper?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 28px 0;">Cheshire house price data continues with town-specific breakdowns, stamp duty calculations, and market timing analysis.</p>
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px;">
        {spokeCards.map((card) => (
          <a href={card.href} class="pillar-card" style="text-decoration: none; display: block;">
            <h3 style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 8px 0; line-height: 1.3;">{card.title}</h3>
            <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: #999999; margin: 0;">{card.description}</p>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Good to Know -->
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="section-inner" style="max-width: 720px;">
      <div style="border-left: 3px solid #3D5A3E; background-color: rgba(61, 90, 62, 0.04); padding: 24px 28px;">
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; color: #3D5A3E; margin: 0 0 8px 0; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em;">Good to know</p>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0;">
          Cheshire house price data on this page combines three sources with different methodologies. ONS UK HPI (December 2025) uses Land Registry completed transactions and reports authority-level averages. Rightmove (12 months to February 2026) uses asking prices and recent sold prices for town-level breakdowns. CW&C Council ward data (2023) uses Land Registry median prices at ward level. ONS figures lag by 2-3 months due to registration delays. Rightmove asking prices run 3-5% above completed transaction prices. Cheshire has 34% detached housing stock versus 22% nationally (Census 2021), which inflates the county average relative to areas with more terraced and flat stock.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related Hubs -->
  <section class="section-pad" style="background-color: #FFFFFF; border-top: 1px solid #E5E0D8;">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-label">Related guides</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">What other Cheshire data helps with a buying decision?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 28px 0;">Cheshire house prices connect to area comparisons, market timing, and purchase process guides across the site.</p>
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px;">
        {relatedHubs.map((hub) => (
          <a href={hub.href} class="pillar-card" style="text-decoration: none; display: block;">
            <div style="width: 36px; height: 36px; background-color: rgba(61, 90, 62, 0.08); border-radius: 6px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0; margin-bottom: 12px;">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#3D5A3E" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d={hub.icon} /></svg>
            </div>
            <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 0 0 6px 0;">{hub.label}</p>
            <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.55; color: #999999; margin: 0;">{hub.description}</p>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
